        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(plugin-sdk): add extensible channel identity hook context",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds extensible channel identity fields to plugin agent hook context: `ctx.senderId`, `ctx.chatId`, `ctx.channel.sender.id`, and `ctx.channel.chat.id`.\n- Threads the transport-native chat id through reply hooks, embedded runs, CLI-backed runs, queued followups, and direct command execution instead of reusing routed reply targets such as `chat:<id>`.\n- Keeps sender/chat identity out of non-user triggered hook contexts and removes the unrelated `SenderSessionKey` session-routing change from this PR.\n- Sets Feishu inbound `conversation.nativeChannelId` from the event `message.chat_id`, so Feishu/Lark-style channel plugins can supply the native group/direct chat id to hooks.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/cli-runner.before-agent-reply-cron.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts src/plugins/hook-agent-context.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.before-agent-reply.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.before-agent-reply-cron.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions.tsbuildinfo`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin hooks can receive channel-scoped sender and transport-native chat identity in a structured extensible context while keeping the existing flat sender ID field.\n\nReal environment tested: local macOS OpenClaw checkout rebased onto latest `upstream/main`, using the repo `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs` wrapper plus core/extensions tsgo checks.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/cli-runner.before-agent-reply-cron.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts src/plugins/hook-agent-context.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.before-agent-reply.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.before-agent-reply-cron.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts`; `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo`; `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions.tsbuildinfo`.\n\nEvidence after fix: 4 Vitest shards passed; 292 tests passed. Core and extensions tsgo checks exited successfully. Local autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: hook context tests prove `channel.sender.id` mirrors `senderId` and `channel.chat.id` mirrors `chatId`; reply, embedded runner, CLI runner, queued followup, direct command, and Feishu inbound tests prove the native chat id is preserved through the relevant runtime hook entry points and omitted for non-user triggers.\n\nWhat was not tested: no live external channel delivery was run in this public branch.\n",
